acoustic set.

36:30.240 --> 36:32.083
Only about 70 people, tops.

36:32.160 --> 36:33.207
Oh, man.

36:33.280 --> 36:34.441
So you're in?

36:40.000 --> 36:42.287
No. Not a Clapton fan.

36:43.360 --> 36:45.010
Think I'll pass.

36:47.200 --> 36:48.486
Okay.

36:48.480 --> 36:51.848
Well, I guess I'll see ya.
Yeah, yeah.

36:51.920 --> 36:53.570
Bye, Lindy.

36:53.640 --> 36:55.927
Oh, did you
see the toe?

36:56.000 --> 36:59.561
Mauricio, I gotta tell
you, you got issues.

36:59.640 --> 37:00.721
Don't even get me started.

37:00.800 --> 37:03.770
Oh, God. There she is.
There's Rosemary.

37:06.160 --> 37:07.366
Where?

37:07.440 --> 37:09.090
Right there.

37:09.160 --> 37:10.127
Right where?

37:10.200 --> 37:12.248
Straight ahead.
Across the field.

37:12.320 --> 37:14.641
Is she behind the rhino?

37:14.720 --> 37:16.722
She's right there!

37:22.960 --> 37:25.884
Mauricio, I want you
to meet someone.

37:25.960 --> 37:30.010
This is Rosemary Shanahan.
Rosemary, Mauricio Wilson.

37:30.080 --> 37:32.651
Hi. Nice to meet you.

37:32.720 --> 37:36.884
Holy cow. I mean, hi.

37:39.760 --> 37:42.081
Is that a Members Only
jacket?

37:42.360 --> 37:43.850
Yes. Yes, it is.

37:43.920 --> 37:45.968
So, are you, like,
the last member?

37:48.720 --> 37:52.406
Oh, man. One-nothing, Rosemary.
I told you she was good.

37:52.480 --> 37:57.088
Excuse me forjust one second.
Hello? Oh, hi, Mom.

37:57.920 --> 38:00.526
Yeah, hold on.
Will you guys excuse me?

38:00.600 --> 38:02.523
Want something
from the snack bar?

38:02.600 --> 38:05.968
Yeah, get me a beer and nachos
with all the stuff on it.

38:06.040 --> 38:07.405
You got it.

38:09.720 --> 38:11.290
Does she take
the cake or what?

38:11.360 --> 38:13.886
She takes
the whole bakery, Hal.

38:13.960 --> 38:15.007
I told you.

38:15.080 --> 38:18.209
Yes, you did. And yet
I wasn't prepared.

38:19.920 --> 38:21.410
So, what are you up for?

38:21.480 --> 38:23.926
I don't know.
I like the track.

38:24.000 --> 38:26.002
So she's a gambler.

38:27.080 --> 38:29.447
Yeah, well, just the dogs.

38:29.520 --> 38:33.002
I hate the ponies. There's too
much human involvement, you know?

38:34.040 --> 38:37.681
You can't trust people if
you're looking for a fair deal.

38:38.960 --> 38:41.440
What about you?
Do you gamble?

38:41.520 --> 38:43.045
No, not really.

38:43.120 --> 38:45.771
I mean, I bet on pro
football now and then,

38:45.840 --> 38:48.605
but to make it more exciting.
I don't care if I win.

38:50.240 --> 38:52.720
I've never read that book.

38:52.800 --> 38:54.165
What book?

38:54.240 --> 38:55.765
<i>Things Losers Say.</i>

38:59.080 --> 39:01.447
Hey, I got a good idea.
Why don't we forget the track,

39:01.520 --> 39:04.524
and I'll introduce you to
some good friends of mine?

39:04.600 --> 39:06.170
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

39:06.280 --> 39:08.169
- All right.
- What do you say?

39:08.280 --> 39:09.566
I say okay.

39:09.640 --> 39:10.880
You say okay?

39:14.240 --> 39:18.564
Hi, guys. I want you to meet a
very good friend of mine. Okay?

39:18.640 --> 39:23.043
This guy here is Hal.
And he's really funny.

39:24.600 --> 39:25.886
- How ya doing?
- Good.

39:25.960 --> 39:27.564
Good to meet ya.

39:29.080 --> 39:30.445
Hey.

39:31.280 --> 39:33.521
Oh, my God.
Look at that face.

39:33.640 --> 39:35.688
She should be doing
Keebler commercials.

39:36.120 --> 39:37.884
You're the cutest thing
I've ever seen.

39:37.960 --> 39:39.610
What's your name,
beautiful?

39:39.680 --> 39:40.681
Cadence.

39:40.760 --> 39:42.888
Cadence.
That's a pretty name.

39:42.960 --> 39:44.803
You know, my uncle's
name is Cadence.

39:46.600 --> 39:49.046
Well, I got news
for you, Cadence.

39:51.600 --> 39:55.571
I'm not putting you down
until the cows come home.

39:55.640 --> 39:57.688
Put her down.

39:58.920 --> 40:00.843
The cow came home.

40:00.960 --> 40:02.769
What is he doing here?

40:02.840 --> 40:04.808
These aren't visiting hours.

40:04.920 --> 40:08.925
Oh, Nurse Peeler, we were just
coming by to say hi to the kids.

40:09.000 --> 40:11.606
Oh, fine.
Pack it up.

40:12.160 --> 40:15.482
And get these patients
back in their beds.

40:20.600 --> 40:21.806
Should we get going?

40:21.880 --> 40:25.487
Don't pay any attention
to Nurse Sourpuss.

40:25.560 --> 40:27.005
Sourpuss.

40:29.640 --> 40:33.247
Heyllgotanidea.
Do you want to play the kissing game?

40:33.320 --> 40:35.402
Me! Idol

40:35.520 --> 40:37.522
Yeah?
Want me to go get a bottle?

40:37.600 --> 40:40.171
No, no. Want to
get the lipstick?

40:40.240 --> 40:41.287
Get lipstick.

40:41.360 --> 40:43.044
Yeah, okay.

40:43.120 --> 40:46.522
What we do is
we put on the lipstick.

40:47.320 --> 40:51.962
The kisser kisses as much as they
can until the lipstick comes off.

40:52.040 --> 40:54.611
Oh, cool.
I want to go first.

40:54.720 --> 40:56.529
Then I'm going last.

40:56.640 --> 40:57.687
Jesse.

40:57.760 --> 40:59.444
Hey,
they don't have

40:59.560 --> 41:01.608
anything I can catch,
do they?

41:01.680 --> 41:03.762
They don't have
anything you can catch.

41:03.840 --> 41:06.605
I didn't think so.
You guys don't even look sick.

41:06.680 --> 41:09.684
You're just a bunch of phonies
like my Uncle Cadence.

41:09.760 --> 41:12.366
I'll bet you're here so you
can get out of school. Right?

41:12.440 --> 41:14.329
- Is that right?
- Yeah.

41:14.400 --> 41:15.401
Give me some lipstick.

41:15.480 --> 41:16.481
Put on lipstick.

41:17.520 --> 41:21.366
You were incredible in there.
You were. You were so amazing.

41:21.440 --> 41:25.331
I'm serious. A lot of people get squeamish
in that situation, and you were so...

41:25.400 --> 41:27.004
Rosemary? Is that you?

41:27.080 --> 41:29.082
Dr. Sayed!
How's it going?

41:29.160 --> 41:30.207
Good. Who is this?

41:30.280 --> 41:31.361
This is my friend Hal.

41:31.440 --> 41:32.771
Hal.
Good to meet you.

41:32.880 --> 41:36.009
Be nice to her.
She's a good girl. All right.

41:36.080 --> 41:38.003
- Bye, Rosemary.
- Bye.

41:38.080 --> 41:40.082
I'm serious. That's what
these kids need,

41:40.160 --> 41:44.165
is, like, a stranger who isn't afraid to
just be with them and play with them.

41:44.240 --> 41:46.368
It builds their
self-confidence.

41:46.480 --> 41:48.562
Why would anybody
be afraid of 'em?

41:49.720 --> 41:53.042
You are off-the-charts adorable.
Do you know that?

41:53.120 --> 41:54.451
Come on.

41:57.440 --> 41:58.851
This is a nice
street you live on.

41:58.920 --> 42:01.924
Yeah, this is my street.
You want to come up?

42:02.040 --> 42:05.965
Yeah. But I don't
think I should.

42:06.040 --> 42:08.611
Why not?
It's only 9:00.

42:08.680 --> 42:10.728
I know. I don't
think it's a good idea.

42:10.880 --> 42:13.690
Oh, no. Did I do something? No.

42:14.960 --> 42:18.009
You've been really cool.

42:18.080 --> 42:19.081
Hi, Hal.

42:19.160 --> 42:22.448
Oh, hey, Jill.
Rosemary, this is my neighbor Jill.

42:22.560 --> 42:23.561
- Hi.
- Hi.

42:23.640 --> 42:25.051
Nice...

42:26.800 --> 42:28.040
Sorry.

42:28.120 --> 42:29.326
Nice to meet you.

42:29.440 --> 42:32.091
Nice to meet you,
too, Jill.

42:32.160 --> 42:36.722
I gotta go meet some friends,
so I'll see you guys later.

42:36.800 --> 42:38.529
- Bye.
- Bye.

42:38.600 --> 42:39.931
Come up.

42:40.920 --> 42:42.888
No.

42:42.960 --> 42:46.567
What? I thought... I thought
we were having a good time.

42:46.640 --> 42:50.087
We were. It's just, you know,
Hal, I'm not used to all this.

42:50.160 --> 42:51.650
Used to what?

42:52.840 --> 42:55.081
Hal, you've been
really nice to me today.

42:55.160 --> 42:56.969
I really appreciate it.
But...

42:57.040 --> 42:59.771
What, your other boyfriends
aren't nice to you?

42:59.840 --> 43:02.161
I don't have
other boyfriends.

43:02.240 --> 43:03.321
Bullshit.

43:08.120 --> 43:10.168
Well, I had one boyfriend.

43:11.520 --> 43:14.251
It was kind of recently, actually,
but it didn't work out.

43:14.360 --> 43:16.362
You've been
burnt?

43:16.840 --> 43:19.764
No. That's just it.

43:19.840 --> 43:23.811
I... I've never been close
enough to anybody to get burnt.

43:23.880 --> 43:27.441
Please! With a mug
like that?

43:27.520 --> 43:29.090
You must be fighting
'em off daily.

43:29.520 --> 43:33.605
Right! I mean, I saw the way your
friend Mauricio looked at me.

43:33.680 --> 43:35.921
I thought he was gonna shoot
me with a tranquilizer gun

43:36.000 --> 43:37.240
and tag my ear.

43:37.320 --> 43:39.926
Don't worry.
He's been acting really weird lately.

43:40.000 --> 43:42.446
Especially around
really pretty girls.

43:44.080 --> 43:45.366
Hal,

43:46.400 --> 43:50.371
do me a favor and stop saying that I'm
pretty, and that I'm not fat, okay?

43:50.480 --> 43:53.450
'Cause it makes me
uncomfortable.

43:53.520 --> 43:55.568
Okay. You have a problem
with compliments?

43:58.200 --> 44:02.000
Look. I know what I am
and I know what I'm not.

44:03.440 --> 44:08.162
I'm the girl who gets really good
grades and isn't afraid to be funny.

44:08.240 --> 44:12.802
And I'm the girl who has a lot of friends
who are boys, and no boyfriends.

44:12.920 --> 44:16.481
I'm not beautiful, okay?
And I never will be.

44:16.560 --> 44:19.484
And I'm fine with that.
You know?

44:20.240 --> 44:24.325
But when you go around saying
that I'm something that I'm not,

44:24.400 --> 44:26.607
it's just,
it's not nice.

44:26.680 --> 44:30.571
Rosemary.
You're starting to scare me.

44:31.240 --> 44:32.685
I mean,
I really like you,

44:32.760 --> 44:38.369
but I have to assume you're a little nutty
if you really believe you're not beautiful.

44:38.440 --> 44:39.680
Grow up, Hal.

44:40.320 --> 44:43.005
Rosie. Wait a second.

44:52.160 --> 44:54.766
Well, it was too
good to be true.

44:56.520 --> 45:00.206
Rosemary. Turned out
to be a total psycho.

45:01.600 --> 45:04.490
Her self-image is
so far off, it's scary.

45:05.520 --> 45:08.763
Well, maybe you had a little
something to do with that.

45:08.840 --> 45:10.604
What? What are you
talking about?

45:10.680 --> 45:14.082
All I ever did was tell her
how perfect she was.

45:14.160 --> 45:16.288
- Really?
- Yeah.

45:16.400 --> 45:18.687
Then she got all huffy
and told me to grow up.

45:19.120 --> 45:22.488
Well, that's probably good advice.
You are kind of immature.

45:24.080 --> 45:27.926
You're not serious. You actually
think you're more mature than me?

45:28.000 --> 45:32.210
Yeah, right. I'm probably
more immature than you,

45:32.280 --> 45:35.011
but at least I have
a bigger willie.

45:43.000 --> 45:45.287
Yeah, bigger
than a mouse's.

45:47.480 --> 45:48.561
What the hell was that?

45:48.680 --> 45:50.364
I said your willie's
bigger than...

45:50.440 --> 45:51.441
I heard,

45:51.560 --> 45:53.801
but it took you,
like, eight seconds.

45:53.880 --> 45:56.087
You can't make a comeback
after eight seconds.

45:56.160 --> 45:59.482
You got three seconds.
Five, tops.

45:59.560 --> 46:03.042
That's why they call it
a quip. Not a slowp.

46:04.520 --> 46:09.003
All right, you got anything better to read?
I gotta fire off a missile.

46:20.480 --> 46:23.529
Hi. Is this
a bad time, or...

46:24.320 --> 46:25.401
No.

46:28.800 --> 46:31.451
I just wanted to apologize
for last night.

46:31.520 --> 46:33.443
You don't have
to apologize.

46:33.800 --> 46:34.961
Yeah, I do.

46:35.040 --> 46:38.487
I called you, like, immature or
sophomoric or something like that.

46:38.560 --> 46:40.927
- I know you're not...
- My God. Hal!

46:41.000 --> 46:43.810
You gotta get in here
and look at this turd.

46:43.880 --> 46:46.406
It looks just like
Klinger from M*A*S*H.

46:50.760 --> 46:53.286
Why don't we get out of here?
Okay.

46:53.360 --> 46:54.805
Coffee?

47:05.160 --> 47:07.003
Excuse me. Are you
ready to order?

47:07.080 --> 47:09.686
Yes. Two double cheeseburgers,
bacon, one with relish.

47:09.760 --> 47:11.489
Thank you.

47:17.040 --> 47:18.121
Are you okay?

47:18.200 --> 47:19.440
Brain freeze.

47:19.760 --> 47:24.721
<i>Baby, now that I've found
you I can't let you go</i>

47:25.000 --> 47:29.289
<i>I'll build my world around
you, I need you so</i>

47:31.280 --> 47:33.521
Excuse me, sweetie.
Professional.

47:40.440 --> 47:42.602
<i>Baby, baby,
since first we met...</i>

47:42.680 --> 47:44.842
Hey, Billy, stay over
near the ladder.

47:45.640 --> 47:48.769
Weak. So weak.

47:48.840 --> 47:51.730
You wanna see a splash?
I'm gonna show you a splash. Ready?

47:56.360 --> 47:59.842
<i>You spend a lifetime
looking for somebody</i>

48:00.480 --> 48:03.006
<i>To give me love like you</i>

48:04.480 --> 48:07.882
<i>Now you've told me
that you wanna leave me</i>

48:07.960 --> 48:11.931
<i>Darling, I just
can't let you</i>

48:12.000 --> 48:16.722
<i>Baby, now that I've found
you I can't let you</i> go...

48:16.800 --> 48:18.484
That was good?

48:18.560 --> 48:19.721
Billy?

48:20.160 --> 48:23.243
Billy? Billy? Billy!

48:24.160 --> 48:25.650
Daddy.

48:29.080 --> 48:30.161
Sorry.

48:30.640 --> 48:33.689
<i>Now that I've found you
I can't let you go</i>

48:33.760 --> 48:37.845
<i>I'll build my world around
you, I need you so</i>

48:38.040 --> 48:41.681
<i>Baby, even though
you don't need</i> me

48:41.760 --> 48:44.570
You don't need me

48:46.480 --> 48:47.720
What's the matter?

48:47.800 --> 48:50.451
I should have
changed at the beach.

48:50.520 --> 48:53.444
What? Are you crazy?
You look great.

48:53.520 --> 48:56.330
I don't normally dress like
this around my parents.

48:56.400 --> 48:57.890
Hey, hey, come on.

48:57.960 --> 49:01.203
I'm the one who should be
nervous here, not you.

49:03.320 --> 49:08.201
Hey, you know, I've been meaning
to ask you, were you adopted?

49:09.200 --> 49:10.770
No. Why?

49:11.480 --> 49:13.926
'Cause your dad
has that weird accent.

49:14.000 --> 49:16.970
And also, I've seen him
around the office.

49:17.040 --> 49:19.122
I gotta say, I don't see
the slightest resemblance.

49:19.200 --> 49:20.361
- Really?
- Yeah.

49:20.440 --> 49:23.603
Everybody says if you put a wig
on him, he'd look just like me.

49:25.520 --> 49:27.682
Would you
look at who's here now?

49:27.760 --> 49:29.046
Come here, my darlin'.

49:29.120 --> 49:30.610
Hi, Daddy.

49:31.200 --> 49:32.167
Rosie, honey.

49:32.280 --> 49:33.520
Mom.

49:33.600 --> 49:35.648
Good to see ya.

49:35.720 --> 49:38.485
Hal Larson, the guy
I was telling you about.

49:38.560 --> 49:39.971
It's great to
meet you, sir.

49:40.080 --> 49:41.684
Likewise.

49:41.760 --> 49:43.091
Nice to meet you, Hal.

49:43.160 --> 49:45.242
The pleasure is mine,
Mrs. Shanahan.

49:46.480 --> 49:49.086
I can see where
Rosemary gets her figure.

49:56.720 --> 50:00.441
What the hell...
What the hell is that you've got on?

50:02.600 --> 50:04.489
We were at the beach.

50:04.560 --> 50:07.723
Won't you be putting
something else on, darlin'?

50:08.720 --> 50:12.805
Oh, come on. She doesn't have to do that for me.
Let's just keep it casual.

50:13.560 --> 50:15.085
Casual.

50:16.840 --> 50:21.368
Hey, Dad, Hal's one of your great
untapped resources down at the company.

50:21.440 --> 50:23.681
Why don't you tell him
some of your ideas?

50:23.760 --> 50:26.764
Oh, so you've got
a few ideas, do ya?

50:27.640 --> 50:29.768
It is risky, but
the rewards are greater, too.

50:29.880 --> 50:33.851
The point is, only a company
with a solid reputation like JPS

50:33.920 --> 50:35.570
could ever market
this product.

50:39.040 --> 50:40.166
Hal, let me take your plate.

50:40.240 --> 50:42.561
Oh, thank you.
It was delicious.

50:42.640 --> 50:44.722
Can I get you boys
some coffee?

50:44.800 --> 50:47.167
I'd love a cup
of tea, darlin'.

50:47.240 --> 50:49.402
Maybe just a drop
of the hard stuff.

50:50.520 --> 50:54.206
Yeah, I'll just have a cup ofjoe.
That'd be great. Thanks.

50:55.560 --> 50:59.770
I have to say, Hal, I'm impressed
with a lot of your ideas.

50:59.840 --> 51:01.968
Some of them are
dog shit, you know,

51:02.040 --> 51:05.283
but for the most part, you seem
to have done your homework.

51:05.360 --> 51:07.727
So I'd like you to do
something for me. Okay.

51:07.800 --> 51:12.010
Well, I'm meeting with me executive
committee Monday morning,

51:12.080 --> 51:14.447
and I'd like you to
make a presentation.

51:15.680 --> 51:17.045
Seriously?

51:17.120 --> 51:19.248
Well, nothing fancy,
you understand.

51:19.320 --> 51:23.041
Just talk about the same things
that you talked about here tonight.

51:23.120 --> 51:24.610
Great. I'd love to.

51:25.040 --> 51:27.042
Oh, and by the way,

51:28.080 --> 51:30.162
you can cut out
the act now.

51:30.240 --> 51:31.241
Excuse me?

51:31.320 --> 51:35.405
You think I got as far as I did
in me life by bein' a fool?

51:36.320 --> 51:39.244
Now, you've got ambition,
Hal, and I admire that.

51:39.320 --> 51:42.449
Hell, I wish I had a hundred
more like yourself.

51:42.520 --> 51:44.488
We'd be the number-one firm
in the country.

51:44.560 --> 51:47.370
And me daughter would get
a hell of a lot more dates.

51:49.120 --> 51:52.169
I'm sure Rosemary doesn't have
any problem getting dates.

51:52.240 --> 51:55.210
I told you to cut
the shit out, all right?

51:55.280 --> 51:58.090
Look, Rosemary
is me daughter,

51:58.160 --> 52:00.288
and God knows
I love her dearly.

52:01.520 --> 52:06.287
But I think we both know that we won't
soon be seeing her twirlin' the baton,

52:06.360 --> 52:08.966
marching along with the
Dallas Cheerleaders.

52:16.880 --> 52:18.723
I don't understand.

52:20.880 --> 52:22.644
I'm telling you
the truth, Hal.

52:23.160 --> 52:27.290
And the truth is I haven't been able
to bounce me daughter on me knee

52:27.360 --> 52:29.362
since she was two.

52:31.240 --> 52:34.289
You know, I've read
about people like you.

52:34.960 --> 52:36.166
People like me?

52:36.240 --> 52:39.323
You superachievers with
your impossible standards.

52:39.400 --> 52:42.483
Nothing's ever good enough.
Nothing measures up.

52:42.560 --> 52:47.168
It never occurs to you that your kids
are people, with their own feelings.

52:47.240 --> 52:48.651
You think they're just
an extension of you,

52:48.720 --> 52:50.529
like your billion-dollar
company,

52:50.600 --> 52:54.889
or your $20 million Lear Jet and
your Picasso out in the front hall.

52:54.960 --> 52:59.284
Everything reflects on you, so nothing
and no one is ever good enough.

53:00.920 --> 53:02.251
Go on.

53:02.560 --> 53:05.006
When I first met Rosemary,

53:05.080 --> 53:07.651
she told me she knew
she wasn't that good-looking.

53:07.720 --> 53:09.609
I could not
believe my ears.

53:10.040 --> 53:12.327
How can a person
this beautiful

53:12.400 --> 53:17.531
possibly interpret what she sees in the
mirror to be anything other than that?

53:17.600 --> 53:19.568
Well, now I know.

53:25.800 --> 53:27.040
Is everything okay?

